MIDRAND - Zimbabwe's first lady Auxiliary Mnangagwa on Monday said she was leaving the Pan African Parliament (PAP) with "a heavy heart" but was moving forward to be a full legislative member of Zimbabwe's new parliament. READ: Mnangagwa launches election campaign "I leave PAP with a heavy heart but having gained much experience. The organisation has helped to mould into the person I am today," she said. She added that her experience with PAP had taught her to follow at times and to lead at other times. She will be leading a new constituency of 16 million people and spearhead several new initiatives in Zimbabwe. READ: Malema, Modise to be sworn in to Pan African Parliament Zimbabwe's first lady added that she pledged full support for the PAP as outlined in Agenda 2063. African News Agency